00:15:51.760 --> 00:15:52.620
- Oh, I see.

00:15:52.620 --> 00:15:55.040
- In other words I hadn't
done all the research,

00:15:55.040 --> 00:15:57.070
I hadn't gone around the world--

00:15:57.070 --> 00:15:58.280
- Looking for evidence.

00:15:58.280 --> 00:15:59.350
- Yes, yes.

00:15:59.350 --> 00:16:01.110
- Okay so...

00:16:01.110 --> 00:16:03.910
- And so socialism is a great idea.

00:16:03.910 --> 00:16:05.810
That does not mean it's a great reality.

00:16:05.810 --> 00:16:09.460
One of the things that disturbs
me tremendously is about

00:16:09.460 --> 00:16:13.100
this enthusiasm for Bernie
Sanders and socialism

00:16:13.100 --> 00:16:16.723
at a time when people are
literally starving in Venezuela,

00:16:16.723 --> 00:16:19.117
an oil-rich country.

00:16:19.117 --> 00:16:23.530
And you know they're
breaking into grocery stores

00:16:23.530 --> 00:16:25.750
to try to get food and they're fleeing

00:16:25.750 --> 00:16:27.100
to neighboring countries,

00:16:27.100 --> 00:16:30.310
most of which are not all
that prosperous themselves,

00:16:30.310 --> 00:16:33.280
but at least you don't
starve to death in them.

00:16:33.280 --> 00:16:35.974
And none of that makes
a bit of difference.

00:16:35.974 --> 00:16:38.030
I don't think most of these
people who are out there

00:16:38.030 --> 00:16:39.550
cheering for Bernie Sanders

00:16:39.550 --> 00:16:42.060
have given a thought to Venezuela.

00:16:42.060 --> 00:16:43.010
- To the evidence.

00:16:43.010 --> 00:16:43.843
- That's right.

00:16:45.873 --> 00:16:50.150
- Which brings us to
something that you refer to

00:16:50.150 --> 00:16:53.400
in a number of columns
as the retrogression.

00:16:53.400 --> 00:16:56.560
The experience of
African-Americans in this country.

00:16:56.560 --> 00:16:59.240
Economic progress, I'm quoting you.

00:16:59.240 --> 00:17:01.930
Despite the grand myth that
black economic progress

00:17:01.930 --> 00:17:04.200
began or accelerated
with the passage of the

00:17:04.200 --> 00:17:07.315
Civil Rights laws and the
'War on Poverty' programs

00:17:07.315 --> 00:17:10.370
of the 1960's, the fact
is that the poverty rate

00:17:10.370 --> 00:17:15.370
among blacks fell from 87%
in 1940 to 47% in 1960,

00:17:15.985 --> 00:17:19.260
but over the next 20 years
the poverty rate among blacks

00:17:19.260 --> 00:17:21.610
fell another 18% points.

00:17:21.610 --> 00:17:25.685
This was just the continuation
of a previous economic trend,

00:17:25.685 --> 00:17:28.940
but at a slower rate of progress.

00:17:28.940 --> 00:17:32.850
It was not some grand deliverance.

00:17:32.850 --> 00:17:34.505
Close quote.

00:17:34.505 --> 00:17:39.505
That is so counter to what
we are taught in school,

00:17:40.140 --> 00:17:43.625
what appears on the editorial
pages of newspapers.

00:17:43.625 --> 00:17:44.880
(laughs)

00:17:44.880 --> 00:17:46.730
I feel as though I want to ask you,

00:17:46.730 --> 00:17:49.979
you really want to stick
with that assertion.

00:17:49.979 --> 00:17:54.070
- I have more evidence
in my most recent book,

00:17:54.070 --> 00:17:56.070
Discrimination and Disparities,

00:17:56.070 --> 00:17:57.920
I point out that this really is a pattern

00:17:57.920 --> 00:18:00.847
not peculiar to blacks or
even to the United States,

00:18:00.847 --> 00:18:03.130
but you can see the same thing in England.

00:18:03.130 --> 00:18:05.730
You can see it in any
number of other countries,

00:18:05.730 --> 00:18:09.310
that the poor we're much
worse off economically.

00:18:09.310 --> 00:18:11.970
Let's say on the first
day after the 20th century

00:18:11.970 --> 00:18:14.620
and yet the in terms of their own behavior

00:18:14.620 --> 00:18:19.564
they were far more decent societies.

00:18:19.564 --> 00:18:24.564
And afterwards, after this welfare state,

00:18:25.060 --> 00:18:26.620
they're supposed to make them better off,

00:18:26.620 --> 00:18:28.870
and better human beings.

00:18:28.870 --> 00:18:31.400
That's when the crime rates skyrocketed

00:18:31.400 --> 00:18:33.053
on both sides of the Atlantic.

00:18:33.902 --> 00:18:36.478
The British were famous for being

00:18:36.478 --> 00:18:41.478
perhaps the most polite,
considerate society in the world

00:18:42.486 --> 00:18:44.084
prior to that.

00:18:44.084 --> 00:18:48.760
After that, you get things
like the 2011 riots over there.

00:18:48.760 --> 00:18:50.780
Went through London Manchester

00:18:50.780 --> 00:18:55.780
where they anticipated
Ferguson and Baltimore

00:18:58.810 --> 00:19:00.290
by a few years.

00:19:00.290 --> 00:19:04.430
And the same things, the
burning down of buildings,

00:19:04.430 --> 00:19:06.800
the throwing of gasoline bombs at police,

00:19:06.800 --> 00:19:09.680
the whole schmear and none of those people

00:19:09.680 --> 00:19:11.030
were descendants of slaves.

00:19:12.260 --> 00:19:15.777
- So poor people were doing things,

00:19:15.777 --> 00:19:18.160
the lesson of the 20th
century is something like

00:19:18.160 --> 00:19:21.300
poor people, including in this
country African-Americans,

00:19:21.300 --> 00:19:22.600
we're improving their lot

00:19:22.600 --> 00:19:24.920
and leading fundamentally decent lives

00:19:24.920 --> 00:19:27.018
until the government decided to help them?

00:19:27.018 --> 00:19:28.700
- Yes.

00:19:28.700 --> 00:19:30.400
- That's a fair statement.

00:19:30.400 --> 00:19:33.361
- They're better off economically

00:19:33.361 --> 00:19:35.710
because of what's been given,

00:19:35.710 --> 00:19:39.141
but of course when you
have the crime rate,

00:19:39.141 --> 00:19:43.030
I mean I got I got the first
inkling of this some years back

00:19:43.030 --> 00:19:46.627
when I was a at some school
in Harlem doing some research

00:19:46.627 --> 00:19:50.560
and I looked out the window
and I mentioned in passing

00:19:50.560 --> 00:19:51.690
that when I was a little kid

00:19:51.690 --> 00:19:54.860
I used to walk my dog in that park

00:19:54.860 --> 00:19:57.681
and looks of horror came
over the students faces.

00:19:57.681 --> 00:20:01.820
Nobody in his right
mind would have a child

00:20:01.820 --> 00:20:05.106
going to that park walking a dog or not.

00:20:05.106 --> 00:20:07.260
The principal was warning these students

00:20:07.260 --> 00:20:09.010
not to cross this park,

00:20:09.010 --> 00:20:11.780
which is about a block a half wide.

00:20:11.780 --> 00:20:13.842
Even in groups of six.

00:20:13.842 --> 00:20:17.970
And when I tell them about
how in these hot summer nights

00:20:17.970 --> 00:20:20.370
I would sleep out on the
fire escapes in Harlem,

00:20:21.210 --> 00:20:23.760
they looked at me like
I was a man from Mars.

00:20:23.760 --> 00:20:26.230
People were are doing
that all over New York.

00:20:26.230 --> 00:20:28.370
They were doing it in
Philadelphia, Washington,

00:20:28.370 --> 00:20:29.900
wherever I've known people.

00:20:29.900 --> 00:20:31.420
That was a common thing.

00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:33.690
We didn't have the money
for air conditioning.

00:20:33.690 --> 00:20:37.090
You slept out and on a fire
escape or in the parks.

00:20:37.090 --> 00:20:38.620
Where Walter grew up in a--

00:20:38.620 --> 00:20:39.530
- Walter Williams.

00:20:39.530 --> 00:20:43.040
- Walter Williams grew
up in a housing project

00:20:43.040 --> 00:20:44.220
in Philadelphia.

00:20:44.220 --> 00:20:47.130
He was saying on the hot summer
nights the people would be,

00:20:47.130 --> 00:20:49.290
in this project we had little balconies,

00:20:49.290 --> 00:20:50.690
they'd sleep out on the balconies

00:20:50.690 --> 00:20:53.380
and the ones on the first
floor who didn't have balconies

00:20:53.380 --> 00:20:55.610
would sleep out in the yard.

00:20:55.610 --> 00:20:58.120
And that there were old
men who you could see sit

00:20:58.120 --> 00:21:00.940
on a hot summer night sitting outdoors

00:21:00.940 --> 00:21:04.987
into the wee hours playing
cards or checkers or whatever.

00:21:04.987 --> 00:21:07.066
it was a different world.

00:21:07.066 --> 00:21:09.000
- It was a safe world.

00:21:09.000 --> 00:21:10.810
- Infinitely safer.

00:21:10.810 --> 00:21:12.140
- Now what about family structure?

00:21:12.140 --> 00:21:13.490
Tom again, I'm quoting you.

00:21:14.363 --> 00:21:15.490
Most black children were being raised in

00:21:15.490 --> 00:21:17.910
two-parent families in 1960.

00:21:17.910 --> 00:21:19.900
30 years after the liberal welfare state,

00:21:19.900 --> 00:21:21.210
the great majority of black children

00:21:21.210 --> 00:21:23.633
were being raised by single parents.

00:21:23.633 --> 00:21:25.670
What's the, how does that,

00:21:25.670 --> 00:21:30.239
by the way we should note
that Patrick Moynihan

00:21:30.239 --> 00:21:34.070
publishes the Moynihan report in 1965

00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:37.800
and he's alarmed because
the illegitimacy rate

00:21:37.800 --> 00:21:41.060
among black families is 25% then.

00:21:41.060 --> 00:21:44.613
Now among whites it's over a third,

00:21:44.613 --> 00:21:47.500
Hispanics it's over half
and among African-Americans

00:21:47.500 --> 00:21:49.030
it's over 70%.

00:21:49.030 --> 00:21:50.600
What's going on there?

00:21:50.600 --> 00:21:52.070
- Well this is again, this too,

00:21:52.070 --> 00:21:54.595
you find the same thing in Britain,

00:21:54.595 --> 00:21:56.410
you find it in France and Norway,

00:21:56.410 --> 00:21:58.060
you find it in the Western world.

00:21:59.140 --> 00:22:00.080
In fact--

00:22:00.080 --> 00:22:01.730
- Their dissolution of
the family structure.

00:22:01.730 --> 00:22:05.000
- Oh yeah, there are a
number of Western nations

00:22:05.000 --> 00:22:09.764
where 40% of the children are
raised with only one parent.

00:22:09.764 --> 00:22:14.764
At the extremes, I
compared Asian countries.

00:22:15.680 --> 00:22:19.670
At the extremes Iceland, it's
two out of three children

00:22:19.670 --> 00:22:22.610
are born are raised in single-parent home.

00:22:22.610 --> 00:22:25.610
In South Korea is one out of 66.

00:22:25.610 --> 00:22:26.443
- Wow.

00:22:27.430 --> 00:22:30.728
Wow and so that's the welfare state?

00:22:30.728 --> 00:22:32.060
- [Tom] Yes.

00:22:32.060 --> 00:22:33.061
- It is.

00:22:33.061 --> 00:22:36.161
- You're creating a situation where the...

00:22:36.161 --> 00:22:41.161
first of all, well you're
creating a situation

00:22:41.199 --> 00:22:43.759
where if the man stays there,

00:22:43.759 --> 00:22:46.942
the government will not
give the woman welfare

00:22:46.942 --> 00:22:50.120
and if he leaves he it will.

00:22:50.120 --> 00:22:51.469
And so they're paying,

00:22:51.469 --> 00:22:54.100
when you pay people not to get married,

00:22:54.100 --> 00:22:55.880
more people don't get married.

00:22:55.880 --> 00:22:57.043
- Right, right.

00:22:57.996 --> 00:22:59.810
Okay so what would have happened

00:23:00.920 --> 00:23:04.200
if Lyndon Johnson instead
of becoming a liberal

00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:09.040
had remained a crusty tough
skeptical Texas conservative,

00:23:09.040 --> 00:23:11.380
which is certainly the
way he started his career.

00:23:11.380 --> 00:23:15.198
If Lyndon Johnson had embraced
the constrained vision

00:23:15.198 --> 00:23:18.480
instead of instituting the war on poverty

00:23:18.480 --> 00:23:20.210
and the Great Society and so forth,

00:23:20.210 --> 00:23:21.990
what would the country look like today?

00:23:21.990 --> 00:23:22.823
- A lot better.

00:23:22.823 --> 00:23:25.530
You would not have the same
rates of crime and so on

00:23:25.530 --> 00:23:28.150
because you see, you
can't have a welfare state

00:23:28.150 --> 00:23:29.740
in a democratic country

00:23:29.740 --> 00:23:32.690
unless you first have
a welfare state vision

00:23:32.690 --> 00:23:36.010
and when you buy all the
assumptions of that vision,

00:23:36.010 --> 00:23:37.830
then you're buying a lot of trouble.

00:23:37.830 --> 00:23:40.100
One of the episodes I think epitomized,

00:23:40.100 --> 00:23:42.200
it was in France in this case,

00:23:42.200 --> 00:23:44.930
that there were knife
attacks by various people

00:23:44.930 --> 00:23:47.480
from North Africa against Chinese people

00:23:47.480 --> 00:23:49.756
in some suburb of Paris.

00:23:49.756 --> 00:23:53.980
And one of the things
that the attacker said,

00:23:53.980 --> 00:23:57.160
you know, why are you
attacking the Chinese?

00:23:57.160 --> 00:23:59.630
And it wasn't because anything
the Chinese had done to them.

00:23:59.630 --> 00:24:02.190
He said they have nice
clothes and big cars,

00:24:02.190 --> 00:24:03.383
that's not fair.

00:24:04.480 --> 00:24:06.188
I mean that's you know,

00:24:06.188 --> 00:24:09.549
egalitarianism as a
philosophy is one thing

00:24:09.549 --> 00:24:12.094
but the actual consequences of it

00:24:12.094 --> 00:24:16.732
mean things like resenting
other people's good fortune.

00:24:16.732 --> 00:24:20.910
- All right so one response to the gap,

00:24:20.910 --> 00:24:24.330
